# 2. 憧れ

Workshop Host: We've invited two guests for the directors' course. One of them happens to be in attendance right now.
Workshop Host: Would you be kind enough to introduce yourself, Mr. Sakaki?
Sakaki: Of course.
ArcLand Cast Member A: Wait... Sakaki? As in...?
ArcLand Director: Y-Yeah...
Sakaki: Hello. I believe I'm meeting most of you for the very first time.
Sakaki: My name is Koryu Sakaki. I'll be one of your teachers during this workshop.
Tsukasa: Koryu Sakaki...?!
Emu: I've seen him on TV before! He's a really famous director, right?
Rui: Yes, he is.
Rui: Koryu Sakaki... Becoming the youngest-ever recipient of the Jiro Kikukawa Award for Theatrical Performances made him a household name.
Rui: He's renowned for his artistry, but he's also known throughout the entertainment industry for his movies and TV dramas...
Tsukasa: Yes, whenever something becomes the talk of the town, you can bet you'll find his name in the credits.
Nene: And he isn't just popular in Japan. He's famous all over the world. Some of the most storied theatres have asked him to produce shows for them.
Nene: I remember reading a magazine article that called him “the busiest director in Japan”...
Emu: Wow. What kind of person do you think he is?
Tsukasa: Well, based on his list of works, he seems like the artistic type with very particular preferences...
Sakaki: I'm really in no position to be teaching anyone anything...
Sakaki: But ArcLand has been so good to me, after all. I couldn't simply turn them down.
Sakaki: In any case, if you find anything I say to be interesting, then I hope you're able to make use of it.
Sakaki: So, let's all do our best together.
Tsukasa: He's much more modest than I was expecting.
Nene: Yeah, I'm a bit surprised...
Rui: (Yes, he seems like an interesting fellow...)
Rui: (Each of Koryu Sakaki's shows is unique in its own way.)
Rui: (It can be the most absurd, impenetrable piece of theatre or a show that's all laughs... Everything that he makes possesses its own “flavor”.)
Rui: (He has an uncanny ability to bring a character's innermost thoughts, good and bad, to the surface, and present them in a fiercely captivating manner.)
Rui: They definitely outdid themselves by bringing him here...
Sakaki: Oh...?
Rui: (...? That expression he just made...)
Nene: Rui? Is something wrong?
Rui: Oh, no. It's nothing.
Rui: (He reminded me of someone else for a second there...)
Rui: (But I might've just been imagining things.)
Workshop Host: Thank you very much, Mr. Sakaki.
Workshop Host: Our second guest will be joining us remotely from abroad due to some scheduling issues.
Workshop Host: He's...
MEIKO: Wow, it sounds like this workshop is going to be incredible!
Tsukasa: Yes! Today was merely the orientation...
Tsukasa: But the venues they've provided and the guests they've invited as teachers are top-class!
Nene: I still can't believe it. This workshop is like a hundred times grander than I was expecting...
Emu: You've looked dazed ever since they finished explaining everything to us, Nene.
Luka: Oh, are you feeling alright?
Nene: I'm fine. I was just a bit overwhelmed...
Nene: But this is also an unbelievably valuable opportunity to learn from world-class professionals.
Tsukasa: Right. We're sure to grow a tremendous amount, as long as we don't shy away from this challenge.
Tsukasa: Let's give it everything we've got!
Emu: Yeah!!
MEIKO: Hehe. You're so motivated!
Rui: ...
Luka: Is something wrong, Rui? Are you feeling sleepy?
Rui: Huh?
Luka: You've looked a little out of it for a while now.
Rui: No, nothing's wrong.
Rui: It's just... Somehow it hasn't entirely sunk in for me, I suppose.
MEIKO: What hasn't sunk in?
Rui: ArcLand invited two guests to come and teach us during this workshop.
Rui: The first is Koryu Sakaki, one of Japan's most renowned directors. The second is...
Director: <It doesn't matter if you're rich or poor, clever or foolish, among the majority or minority...>
Director: <All people laugh, cry and feel anger in the same way...>
Director: <That is what ties us all together after bearing witness to a truly marvelous spectacle.>
Director: <My goal is to keep making shows that do just that.>
Director: <I believe that is the key to humanity becoming one... I believe that there's something unimaginably special awaiting us at the end of that path!>
Little Rui: ...
Rui: Tom Gray.
Rui: A director I admire very much.
Luka: So Rui, you get to be taught by your hero?
Rui: Yes, so it seems. Perhaps that's why nothing has felt quite real all afternoon.
Tsukasa: I understand exactly how you feel!
Tsukasa: I thought I was dreaming when I heard that Mr. Amami had come to see our show!
Rui: Hehe. I remember. It's difficult to believe that these things could actually happen.
Rui: If I could somehow tell my younger self this would happen, I'm sure he wouldn't believe me.
MEIKO: I see... This Mr. Gray really means a lot to you, doesn't he?
Luka: Hehe. I wish I could tell little Rui the good news.
Luka: Did you know? In the future, you'll work very, very hard...
Luka: And someday, you'll get to meet your hero! That's what I would say.
Tsukasa: Opportunity has come knocking, Rui!
Tsukasa: I understand what you're feeling, but you need to focus and make this most of this golden opportunity!
Emu: You've got this, Rui!
Luka: Zzz... Zzz...
Luka: Rui... I believe in you...♪
MEIKO: That was pretty clear, for sleep talk.
Rui: Hehe...
Rui: Thank you all very much. I plan on learning as much as I possibly can.
